  {
    "user": "U07BD7U4S4R",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1754659752.838499",
    "client_msg_id": "e8ec1c92-ca82-4925-9a21-d2fe1277497d",
    "text": "1. if you need to run program and wait for it to finish to know whether it halts or not (sync) – language of test implementation and running it in different process/machine - is irrelevant. \n2. if you think you can tell just by analyzing source code (async): if program involves any outside data – there is always a chance an irreducible computation is required, which can be done only by running program, goto 1.\n",
